                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3393: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fuller</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-16T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1920—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 16—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Telegraphic and telephone communication with Peking interrupted. Railway
                    communication interrupted since July 15, 10 p.m. by fighting between Chinese
                    factions. Consular body considering measures keep fighting away from Tientsin.
                    International investigating expedition proceeding along railway tonight.
                    Wireless communication open.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fuller</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
